nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So if North had a marginal bid, he would choose the more conservative action and perhaps pass or bid less than he would otherwise. However, you should preempt whenever you have a suitable hand. If you wait for the ideal hand you will never preempt.|
